cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper discusses a tool chain for improving privacy on Android smartphones through runtime monitoring and in-vivo bytecode instrumentation. The paper focuses on the security and software engineering aspects of the tool chain, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of running powerful runtime monitoring and instrumentations directly on smartphones, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
